# initial_program.py

import random

# EVOLVE-BLOCK-START
def run_search():
    n = 47
    # all grid points
    grid = [(x,y) for x in range(n) for y in range(n)]
    S = []
    #random.shuffle(grid) # Remove shuffling for better initial distribution
    for (x,y) in grid:
        ok = True
        # check collinearity against every pair already in S
        for i in range(len(S)):
            for j in range(i + 1, len(S)):
                x1, y1 = S[i]
                x2, y2 = S[j]
                # Check if (x, y), (x1, y1), and (x2, y2) are collinear
                if (y - y1) * (x2 - x1) == (y2 - y1) * (x - x1):
                    ok = False
                    break
            if not ok:
                break

        if ok:
            S.append((x,y))
    return S
# EVOLVE-BLOCK-END
